		<p id="welcome"><div style="float: left;"><a title="Loci areas" href="#morefeaturesbottom"><em>Loci</em> areas</a></div>
<div style="float: right;">ISSN 1941-9198</div>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p style="clear: both;"><span style="font-size: small;">Welcome to <em>Loci</em>,&#160;the online publication of the<br /><a href="/">Mathematical Sciences Digital Library</a>&#160;(MathDL).</span></p>
<p><em>Loci</em> Areas: <a href="/mathDL/46/">Convergence</a>, <a href="/mathDL/47/">Resources</a>, <a href="/mathDL/55/">Developers</a>, <a href="/mathDL/54/">Departments</a></p>
<p>In <a href="/mathDL/56/">Announcements</a> Department:<br />&#160;<a href="/mathDL/56/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=3566">MAA and <em>Loci</em> on Facebook</a></p>
<p>In <a href="/mathDL/57/">Commentaries</a> Department:<br /> &#160;&#160;"<a href="/mathDL/57/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=3489">What Does the iPad Mean for Math?</a>" by Thomas E. Leathrum</p>
<p>In&#160;<a href="/mathDL/60/">Supplements</a> Department:<br /> &#160;&#160; <a href="/mathDL/60/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=3404">Supplement to 'Fermat's Spiral and the Line Between Yin and Yang'</a><br />&#160;&#160;&#160;(accompanies article in November 2010 <em>American Mathematical Monthly</em>)</p>
<p><a href="/mathDL/23/?pa=content&amp;sa=viewDocument&amp;nodeId=3360"><em>Loci</em>&#160; Volume 1 Table of Contents</a></p>
<p>Try the "Show MAA on Twitter" button <a href="#togdiv">below</a></p></p>







            


